{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryAdvancedUsage","doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryTesting","doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryPerformance","doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/SwiftDataMigrations"],"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQuery"],"anchor":"Live-Queries","title":"Live Queries"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable","doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/liveQueryContext"],"anchor":"Dependency-Setup","title":"Dependency Setup"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/SwiftDataHelpersModelContext"],"anchor":"Structures","title":"Structures","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftDataHelpers is a small, focused package that collects convenience APIs for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"working with SwiftData in SwiftUI apps. The goal is to keep common patterns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simple, readable, and testable."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Today the library focuses on live SwiftUI queries powered by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift-dependencies"},{"type":"text","text":", and it will expand with more helpers over time as new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"needs appear."}]},{"anchor":"Requirements","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Requirements"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS 17, macOS 14, watchOS 10, tvOS 17, visionOS 2"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift tools version 6.2"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftData (Apple framework, available on the platforms above)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Dependencies","type":"heading","text":"Dependencies","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-dependencies","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftData (Apple framework)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Get-Started","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Get Started"},{"anchor":"Add-the-package-in-Xcode","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Add the package in Xcode"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open your project in Xcode and choose File > Add Packages."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enter "},{"code":"https:\/\/github.com\/vadimkrutovlv\/swift-data-helpers.git","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Select the "},{"code":"SwiftDataHelpers","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" product and add it to your target."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"anchor":"Add-the-package-in-Swift-Package-Manager","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Add the package in Swift Package Manager"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Package.swift","","dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/vadimkrutovlv\/swift-data-helpers.git\", from: \"1.0.0\")","],","","targets: [","    .target(","        name: \"YourApp\",","        dependencies: [\"SwiftDataHelpers\"]","    )","]"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Update the version as new releases are published."}]},{"anchor":"Using-LiveQuery","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Using LiveQuery"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a SwiftUI property wrapper that keeps your view state in sync"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with SwiftData. It refreshes when the underlying model container saves, so your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lists and sections stay current without manual fetch logic."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It can be thought of as an alternative to SwiftData’s "},{"code":"@Query","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" macro, with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"explicit dependency-based context configuration."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also use "},{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" models (for example, a feature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"model that owns shared data) and any other main-actor-isolated type where you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want live SwiftData-backed state."}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using "},{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" inside an "},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" model, mark the property"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with "},{"code":"@ObservationIgnored","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to avoid conflicts with the Observation framework:"}]},{"code":["@Observable","final class MyFeatureModel {","    @ObservationIgnored","    @LiveQuery var items: [Item]","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}]},{"anchor":"Configure-the-ModelContext-primary","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Configure the ModelContext (primary)"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" relies on the Dependencies value "},{"code":"liveQueryContext.modelContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Configure it once at your app entry point so every view has a consistent source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of truth. This is the recommended setup for most apps."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you do not already have a container, create a main container up front and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pass its "},{"code":"mainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" into the dependency:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import Dependencies","import SwiftData","import SwiftDataHelpers","import SwiftUI","","@main","struct MyApp: App {","    let container: ModelContainer = try! ModelContainer(","        for: Person.self","    )","","    init() {","        let container = self.container","        prepareDependencies {","            $0.liveQueryContext.modelContext = { container.mainContext }","        }","    }","","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            ContentView()","                .modelContainer(container)","        }","    }","}"]},{"anchor":"Use-LiveQuery","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Use @LiveQuery"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" keeps SwiftUI in sync with SwiftData by refreshing when the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"underlying container saves. You can pass a predicate and sort descriptors to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"filter and order results."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import SwiftDataHelpers","import SwiftUI","","struct PeopleList: View {","    @LiveQuery(","        predicate: #Predicate<Person> { $0.isActive },","        sort: [SortDescriptor(\\Person.name)]","    )","    private var people: [Person]","","    var body: some View {","        List(people) { person in","            Text(person.name)","        }","    }","}"]},{"anchor":"Consume-LiveQuery-as-AsyncStream","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Consume LiveQuery as AsyncStream"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"code":"$people.valuesStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when you need async iteration over snapshots:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@MainActor","@Observable","final class PeopleFeatureModel {","    @ObservationIgnored","    @LiveQuery(sort: [SortDescriptor(\\Person.name)])","    var people: [Person]","","    @ObservationIgnored","    private var valuesTask: Task<Void, Never>?","","    func observePeople() {","        valuesTask?.cancel()","        valuesTask = Task {","            for await snapshot in $people.valuesStream {","                print(\"People count: \\(snapshot.count)\")","            }","        }","    }","","    deinit {","        valuesTask?.cancel()","    }","}"]},{"anchor":"Multiple-Containers-optional","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Multiple Containers (optional)"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your app uses more than one "},{"code":"ModelContainer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (for example, main and private"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stores), use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable"},{"type":"text","text":" to scope queries to the desired container."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is ideal for subtrees of your UI that should read from a non-default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"container."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["LiveQueryBindable(modelContainer: .privatePersons) {","    PrivatePeopleView()","}"]},{"anchor":"Previews-and-Tests-optional","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Previews and Tests (optional)"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For previews and tests, inject a "},{"code":"ModelContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. This keeps "},{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functional without bootstrapping your full app lifecycle."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["#Preview {","    prepareDependencies {","        $0.liveQueryContext.modelContext = { ModelContainer.main.mainContext }","    }","","    return PeopleList()","        .modelContainer(.main)","}"]},{"anchor":"FAQ","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"FAQ"},{"anchor":"I-see-logs-about-liveQueryContextmodelContext-not-set-What-does-it-mean","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"I see logs about `liveQueryContext.modelContext` not set. What does it mean?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" requires a "},{"code":"ModelContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/liveQueryContext"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If this dependency is not configured, SwiftDataHelpers logs a fault and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"query returns empty results until a context is provided. Configure it once at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"your app entry point with "},{"code":"prepareDependencies","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", or scope a subtree with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Can-I-use-LiveQuery-outside-of-views","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Can I use `@LiveQuery` outside of views?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes. It works in "},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" models or other main-actor-isolated types. When"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"used inside an observable model, mark the property wrapper with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"@ObservationIgnored","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to avoid conflicts with Observation."}]},{"anchor":"How-do-I-query-multiple-containers","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"How do I query multiple containers?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable"},{"type":"text","text":" to scope queries to a specific container, or override"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the dependency for a particular subtree. The advanced guide shows patterns for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"main\/private container setups."}]},{"anchor":"Is-LiveQuery-a-replacement-for-Query","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Is `@LiveQuery` a replacement for `@Query`?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is an alternative with explicit dependency-based context configuration. If"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you prefer SwiftData’s "},{"code":"@Query","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" macro, you can continue using it alongside this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"library."}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftdatahelpers"]}],"metadata":{"role":"collection","externalID":"SwiftDataHelpers","symbolKind":"module","modules":[{"name":"SwiftDataHelpers"}],"title":"SwiftDataHelpers","roleHeading":"Framework"},"abstract":[{"type":"t